window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>Wipeout of the Wireless Weenies</i> is the seventh collection of spooky short stories for ages eight to 12 by the beloved author of the Nathan Abercrombie series, David Lubar. This is the perfect pick for reluctant young leaners who like a few chills and a lot of laughs. </p> <p>Welcome to the Weenie Zone! A boy and his family narrowly escape a zombie apocalypse - or do they? A girl neglects her cat's litter box and finds herself in a heap of trouble. And a group of clicking, scrolling, tapping wireless weenies find themselves on the edge of disaster. </p> <p>Here are 33 hilarious and harrowing stories that will scare you, make you laugh, or see the world in a whole new way. Find out where the author got the idea for each story at the end of the book. Don't be a weenie. Listen to these stories. If you dare!</p>"; 
